ActivityCommentText: Organization ActivityID=HALE_0120151103_E351B181-2
ResultCommentText: South shore of Lake Waielele. Very marshy around lake. Holcus lanatus (velvet grass), sedge, carax, ohia trees, olapa, and melacope surround lake and hang over edge of lake. Two green swords at edge of lake also Kolea present. Tufts of filamentous algae in lake at edges. Odate larvae (large) seen in lake. Visually saw black and yellow striped odonate larvae on edge.
